    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm also in favor of greedy as the default. I think it encourages more slashers on the network, whilst still allowing concerned entities to be altruistic.\r\n\r\nAnother, more complex option would be to switch on `eth1_chain.is_some()`:\r\n\r\n- `true`: we probably have stakers. Keep slashings private unless `--broadcast-slashings true`.\r\n- `false`: probably no stakers. Publish slashings unless `--broadcast-slashings false`.\r\n\r\nI'm not convinced the more complex version is worth it though, I prefer a single opt-in flag.",
